<!doctype linuxdoc system>

<article>
<title> Information for S3 ViRGE and ViRGE/VX Users
<author>The XFree86 Project Inc.
<date>22 January 1997
<toc>

<sect> Supported hardware
<p>
The current XF86_S3V server supports S3 ViRGE (86C325) and 
S3 ViRGE/VX (86C988) chips.  32bpp TrueColor and External RAMDACs for 
ViRGE/VX are not yet supported.  It has been tested with ViRGE cards with
2 and 4MB DRAM and with a 220MHz ViRGE/VX card with 2MB VRAM up to 
1600x1200 with 8/15/16bpp.

For 3.2A, the server supports 24 bpp.  It is reported to lock video on
ViRGE/VX chipsets when run twice, and dump core with some setups.  It
appears stable on ViRGE chipsets.  There are known problems, but you
should be able to run xterms and applications that support 24 bpp or
Truecolor.  Known exceptions include xanim (reported patch fixes this), 
netscape, xfig, and xfishtank.  (and others...)

NOTE: This driver is pretty new, and not everything might work like you expect
it to. It shouldn't crash your machine, but you may have video artifacts
or missing lines. Please report any and all problems to
<htmlurl name="XFree86@Xfree86.org" url="mailto:XFree86@Xfree86.org">
using the appropriate bug report sheet. 

There will be updated drivers in the coming XFree86 beta releases. 

<sect>Features:
<p>

<itemize>
<item> Basic support for S3 ViRGE and ViRGE/VX video adapters
<item> uses linear frame buffer
<item> it should be possible to reach resolutions up to 2048x2048
<item> it should be possible to use pixel depths of 8, 15, 16, and 24 
  (32 not yet) bits
  per pixel.
</itemize>

<sect>Future Features (in order from highest to lowest priority)
<p>

<itemize>
<item>	improved support of 24, support of 32bpp
<item>	some more hardware acceleration
<item>	3d acceleration (once we work out how that's done)
<item>  more chipsets and RAMDACs
</itemize>

<sect>Configuration:
<p>

The server auto-detects RAM size, RAMDAC and ClockChip. Do not bother putting 
these in your "Device" section. 
The "nolinear" option is unsupported.		   

<sect>Known problems with 24 bpp:
<p>

<itemize>
<item> Mode switching is bad!  You may corrupt your text console if you mode
switch.  Avoid use of Ctl-Alt-+ and Ctl-Alt-'-'.
<item> ViRGE/VX may dump core.
<item> ViRGE/VX may lock the server if run twice with a machine reset.
</itemize>

